EmailTemplate.subject: Counterparty Manager Next Steps
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Greetings,
Thank you for joining Counterparty Manager and Tax Utility, a secure and centralized location for your end to end client onboarding and lifecycle management needs. To get started, please reply with the below information to be uploaded and provided to your brokers. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to reach out to us. Contact details are provided at the end of the email.
1. List of Active Broker Dealers Please refer to the attached list and provide the Broker Dealers which you would like to share information with through Counterparty Manager and Tax Utility
2. Entity Data In addition to your entity, please provide the information listed below for any parent company, investment management entity, controlled or additional operating entities: True/Legal Name Country/Territory of Domicile Entity Type (e.g. Corporation, Fund, Investment Management Company, etc.) Products/transaction types planned for the entities Note: please provide this information through email or by using the entity bulk upload template available here.
3. User Details Please provide the details below for each user you would like to be set up with access to Counterparty Manager and Tax Utility Full Name Email Address (we do not accept group email addresses) Title/Position Business Address Phone Number
4. Entity Documentation Please provide formation and tax documents for each entity listed. This could include but is not limited to: Articles of Incorporation Certificate of Registration Tax Form (i.e. W-9/W-8 etc.)
5. AUM/NAV Information If any of the entities provided are investment managers, please provide the below information: Current AUM / NAV Currency (USD / EUR / etc.) As of Date
6. Would you like to hear more about our full suite of solutions? Our solution set is built to make day to day processes more efficient and secure. We offer services across Client Onboarding, Account Opening, Corporate Onboarding, Client Lifecycle Management, KYC, Tax, and Client Outreach processes. Fact sheets attached herein provide further detail.
Upon completion of the above, each user will receive a welcome email with login credentials. Regulatory information can be completed for Dodd Frank Protocols, EMIR Classifications, Canadian Representation Letter, Cross Border Representation, Australian Single Sided Reporting Rules, Initial Margin Segregation and/or other ISDA Amend Protocol questionnaires.
For any questions or assistance with any of the above, please do not hesitate to reach out to our support team via email at mcpmsupport@ihsmarkit.com or by telephone:
Counterparty Manager Hotline UK: + 44 (0) 207 260 2102 Counterparty Manager Hotline US: + 1 212 488 4049 Counterparty Manager Hotline Singapore: + 65 6922 4258
